323
00:21:12,903 --> 00:21:14,872
(6 sausages, 5 cup noodles, 10 biscuits...)

324
00:21:14,873 --> 00:21:15,944
What about my sausages?

325
00:21:16,174 --> 00:21:18,184
Low-balance alert.

326
00:21:23,254 --> 00:21:24,254
Hold on.

327
00:21:27,623 --> 00:21:28,893
This punk.

328
00:21:29,623 --> 00:21:32,663
(Seoyoung Studio)

329
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:40,333
Introduce me to that hacker.

330
00:21:40,573 --> 00:21:43,004
That's a big favour for a cup of coffee.

331
00:21:44,444 --> 00:21:45,444
Is it?

332
00:21:45,744 --> 00:21:48,313
I'm a lawyer who works for you with zero legal fees.

333
00:21:49,143 --> 00:21:50,413
Should we do the math?

334
00:21:51,343 --> 00:21:53,514
I'm a client who you screwed over.

335
00:21:53,813 --> 00:21:55,184
I could report you to the disciplinary committee.

336
00:21:55,484 --> 00:21:56,853
Let's write an official complaint, then.

337
00:21:59,724 --> 00:22:01,153
Next time, start by threatening me.

338
00:22:01,623 --> 00:22:03,224
Don't be pretentious and act like you're asking for a favour.

339
00:22:03,424 --> 00:22:04,893
You asked if the law was my weapon, right?

340
00:22:05,194 --> 00:22:07,163
I have no weapon. All I have are weaknesses.

341
00:22:07,363 --> 00:22:08,893
So, I'm going to need some help.

342
00:22:15,573 --> 00:22:16,643
Welcome.

343
00:22:22,313 --> 00:22:23,984
Ms. Lee Ro Um told me about you.

344
00:22:28,094 --> 00:22:29,794
(Dajung Comic Books)

345
00:22:29,795 --> 00:22:31,295
A digital funeral?

346
00:22:32,124 --> 00:22:33,134
Yes.

347
00:22:36,035 --> 00:22:38,604
Didn't she tell you about what I do?

348
00:22:39,634 --> 00:22:41,005
She only told me that you were a hacker.

349
00:22:45,104 --> 00:22:47,414
It's a little different from my usual work,

350
00:22:47,815 --> 00:22:49,944
but I'll do it for Ro Um.

351
00:22:50,315 --> 00:22:52,215
Do you need a funeral of your own?

352
00:22:53,215 --> 00:22:54,215
No.

353
00:22:54,414 --> 00:22:56,725
The phone that Ro Um sent data to.

354
00:22:57,985 --> 00:22:59,955
The ones who were being blackmailed.

355
00:23:00,255 --> 00:23:04,094
Please delete their videos and info on the Internet.

356
00:23:05,394 --> 00:23:06,434
Why?

357
00:23:10,035 --> 00:23:12,035
I was wondering why you'd care.

358
00:23:12,334 --> 00:23:13,575
There were a lot of them.

359
00:23:15,475 --> 00:23:17,874
I'll pay the adequate amount, so please take care of it.

360
00:23:22,374 --> 00:23:25,644
I can find the same videos online to delete them,

361
00:23:26,045 --> 00:23:27,683
ask them to delete personal information,

362
00:23:27,684 --> 00:23:29,255
and monitor the websites for a while.

363
00:23:29,555 --> 00:23:30,755
That's all I can do for you.

364
00:23:31,025 --> 00:23:33,094
I can't get to personal clouds or the deep web.

365
00:23:33,225 --> 00:23:35,394
That's much better than what I can do.

366
00:23:36,965 --> 00:23:38,024
Please do that.

367
00:23:38,025 --> 00:23:39,795
The other part sounded like the police's job.

368
00:23:41,894 --> 00:23:42,894
What's wrong?

369
00:23:44,364 --> 00:23:45,364
Nothing.

370
00:23:46,065 --> 00:23:48,104
I'll look into it and call you.

371
00:23:48,874 --> 00:23:51,075
How do you know Ms. Lee?

372
00:23:52,245 --> 00:23:55,414
Oh, we were prison cell mates.

373
00:23:56,444 --> 00:23:57,485
I see.

374
00:23:58,844 --> 00:24:00,714
You're helping her?

375
00:24:00,715 --> 00:24:01,854
Yes, that's right.

376
00:24:02,515 --> 00:24:03,555
There's no way...

377
00:24:05,354 --> 00:24:06,894
she told you that.

378
00:24:07,094 --> 00:24:08,825
She doesn't care at all about me.

379
00:24:11,825 --> 00:24:15,694
You must care a lot about her, though.

380
00:26:01,705 --> 00:26:03,874
What? You can't do it?

381
00:26:04,545 --> 00:26:07,975
Stay awake. I'm always watching.

382
00:26:41,144 --> 00:26:43,285
- Han Moo Young. - What?

383
00:26:44,444 --> 00:26:48,584
We negotiated the settlement from 50,000 down to 5,000 dollars.

384
00:26:50,025 --> 00:26:52,624
Don't I deserve some acknowledgement?

385
00:26:53,225 --> 00:26:54,725
Are you talking about Seo Gye Sook?

386
00:26:56,295 --> 00:26:57,465
What about her son's case?

387
00:27:03,364 --> 00:27:04,364
You...

388
00:27:06,005 --> 00:27:07,035
You really...

389
00:27:08,174 --> 00:27:11,144
Your mind is all over the place, isn't it?

390
00:27:11,975 --> 00:27:14,275
The case was closed.

391
00:27:14,815 --> 00:27:15,874
The insurance...

392
00:27:16,344 --> 00:27:18,444
was paid out long ago.

393
00:27:19,684 --> 00:27:21,315
What do you mean the case was closed?

394
00:27:26,055 --> 00:27:29,995
It was concluded an accidental death.

395
00:27:31,124 --> 00:27:33,394
An accidental death? What about the insurance?

396
00:27:34,035 --> 00:27:37,505
What 18-year-old pays 2,000 dollars a month in premiums?

397
00:27:37,965 --> 00:27:39,535
They were all life insurance policies.

398
00:27:41,775 --> 00:27:44,144
I did all I could do.

399
00:27:45,904 --> 00:27:49,244
The case was closed, but Seo Gye Sook kept protesting...

400
00:27:49,245 --> 00:27:50,814
and acting out,

401
00:27:50,815 --> 00:27:52,215
and I had to stop her.

402
00:27:52,914 --> 00:27:56,584
As I just said, I negotiated the settlement down to a tenth.

403
00:27:56,785 --> 00:27:58,285
What more should I do?

404
00:27:58,755 --> 00:28:00,154
Investigate the death?

405
00:28:01,424 --> 00:28:03,995
Do you admit that I did enough?

406
00:28:04,194 --> 00:28:07,864
As a lawyer, I did all I could do within my legal capacity.

407
00:28:08,035 --> 00:28:10,433
Seo Gye Sook said she'd rather...

408
00:28:10,434 --> 00:28:12,265
go to prison than settle,

409
00:28:13,035 --> 00:28:14,834
and she's your problem now.

410
00:28:26,914 --> 00:28:28,584
What on earth happened?

411
00:28:28,914 --> 00:28:30,424
What a mess.

412
00:28:30,825 --> 00:28:33,623
Don't even ask. It's a disaster zone.

413
00:28:33,624 --> 00:28:35,424
Was there no maintenance done?

414
00:28:41,965 --> 00:28:45,305
Everything here's a mess.

415
00:29:07,295 --> 00:29:09,054
(Case Consultation Record)

416
00:29:09,055 --> 00:29:10,725
(Valley Death Case Report)

417
00:29:12,795 --> 00:29:14,664
(Investigative points)

418
00:29:21,874 --> 00:29:23,173
Han Moo Young speaking.

419
00:29:23,174 --> 00:29:25,174
I did everything you asked me to.

420
00:29:25,644 --> 00:29:28,015
Thanks a lot, Da Jung.

421
00:29:28,644 --> 00:29:30,344
I'll pay you the outstanding amount.

422
00:29:30,745 --> 00:29:32,584
- Are you at home? - Yes.

423
00:29:34,854 --> 00:29:36,755
Am I being traced?

424
00:29:38,384 --> 00:29:39,555
Something like that.

425
00:29:52,864 --> 00:29:53,904
Ro Um.

426
00:29:57,305 --> 00:29:58,374
For rent.

427
00:30:03,515 --> 00:30:05,684
Is something wrong? Were you out?

428
00:30:07,285 --> 00:30:09,854
The studio's flooded. Take the money.

429
00:30:13,055 --> 00:30:14,094
Take it.

430
00:30:15,955 --> 00:30:18,394
Why would I? This isn't a hotel.

431
00:30:19,265 --> 00:30:20,265
Come in.

432
00:31:04,944 --> 00:31:06,444
How long will you keep staring?

433
00:31:31,235 --> 00:31:33,434
What are you looking at? Stop looking.

434
00:31:42,344 --> 00:31:44,785
(Yoo Myung Hoon had multiple life insurance policies.)

435
00:31:48,755 --> 00:31:49,815
What's that?

436
00:31:53,025 --> 00:31:55,694
A suspected insurance fraud case.

437
00:31:55,825 --> 00:31:58,294
(Yoo Myung Hoon had multiple life insurance policies.)

438
00:31:58,295 --> 00:31:59,825
The adopted kid's accidental death?

439
00:32:00,235 --> 00:32:01,535
It was in the news.

440
00:32:01,965 --> 00:32:03,765
A grown kid got adopted out.

441
00:32:05,005 --> 00:32:07,305
To a friend the mother trusted.

442
00:32:09,174 --> 00:32:10,404
Then why is it fraud?

443
00:32:12,245 --> 00:32:14,214
A guy who couldn't swim was found in deep waters...

444
00:32:14,215 --> 00:32:16,114
without any safety equipment.

445
00:32:16,844 --> 00:32:18,614
He had 15 life insurance policies.

446
00:32:19,344 --> 00:32:21,784
Did his adoptive parents sell insurance?

447
00:32:21,785 --> 00:32:23,315
The woman's sibling did.

448
00:32:24,084 --> 00:32:25,284
How could you tell?

449
00:32:25,285 --> 00:32:27,694
Insurance fraud requires someone with experience.

450
00:32:28,455 --> 00:32:29,455
Were they caught?

451
00:32:30,594 --> 00:32:31,594
No.

452
00:32:32,295 --> 00:32:34,234
The death was ruled accidental,

453
00:32:34,235 --> 00:32:36,065
and the insurance money was paid out.

454
00:32:36,565 --> 00:32:39,465
- Then it's over. - Not yet.

455
00:32:39,934 --> 00:32:42,735
The birth mother refuses to settle, and I'm helping her.

456
00:32:46,344 --> 00:32:48,613
You're helping her refuse to settle?

457
00:32:48,614 --> 00:32:50,285
I should help her settle.

458
00:32:51,245 --> 00:32:53,714
It'll get even harder if the defamation charge sticks.

459
00:32:53,715 --> 00:32:55,315
Why is she refusing to settle?

460
00:32:55,684 --> 00:32:56,684
Because she's penniless?

461
00:32:57,955 --> 00:32:59,255
Because of her son.

462
00:33:00,025 --> 00:33:03,025
If she settles, it means admitting the adoptive parents were right.

463
00:33:04,225 --> 00:33:06,124
The truth will be buried.

464
00:33:06,295 --> 00:33:08,565
See if you can say that for a smaller amount of money.

465
00:33:09,565 --> 00:33:12,805
It's not about money. I want to fight to the end.

466
00:33:14,035 --> 00:33:15,075
"Fight?"

467
00:33:15,634 --> 00:33:19,144
It looks like you're whining, keeping the neighbourhood awake.

468
00:33:20,005 --> 00:33:21,744
If someone killed your child,

469
00:33:21,745 --> 00:33:23,883
you must gouge out their eyes and dig out their heart...

470
00:33:23,884 --> 00:33:25,644
in front of their family.

471
00:33:25,745 --> 00:33:28,854
That's what you must do to call yourself family.

472
00:33:29,285 --> 00:33:30,883
If you thought someone else...

473
00:33:30,884 --> 00:33:33,285
could do a better job raising your child,

474
00:33:33,525 --> 00:33:35,394
whether it ends in abuse or murder,

475
00:33:35,654 --> 00:33:37,325
that's what you must live with.

476
00:33:37,995 --> 00:33:40,124
Her kid died because of the choice she made.

477
00:33:41,434 --> 00:33:43,634
Expecting society to pay the price...

478
00:33:45,134 --> 00:33:46,265
is cowardice.

479
00:33:48,604 --> 00:33:49,634
Go tell her.

480
00:33:50,205 --> 00:33:52,744
If she has a conscience, she should know...

481
00:33:52,745 --> 00:33:54,875
to gladly pay the consequences for her own actions,

482
00:33:55,745 --> 00:33:57,185
even if it leads to pure misery.

483
00:33:57,745 --> 00:33:58,785
Ro Um.

484
00:34:01,614 --> 00:34:04,685
No one can pay the consequences for their every action.

485
00:34:06,424 --> 00:34:08,125
That's why we all need others.

486
00:34:12,165 --> 00:34:14,335
What can other people do for her?

487
00:34:17,364 --> 00:34:18,734
No matter how difficult the situation is,

488
00:34:19,504 --> 00:34:21,504
I'll fight alongside her to the end.

489
00:34:41,194 --> 00:34:42,495
Your dad and I came to get you.

490
00:34:43,294 --> 00:34:44,325
Come with us.

491
00:34:46,064 --> 00:34:47,134
Let's go home.

492
00:34:49,694 --> 00:34:51,705
- Ro Um... - Ro Um.

493
00:34:52,835 --> 00:34:53,835
- No! - Ro Um...

494
00:35:54,564 --> 00:35:56,995
(Complaint)

495
00:35:57,935 --> 00:35:59,105
What a joke.

496
00:36:03,174 --> 00:36:05,145
(Complaint)

497
00:36:06,745 --> 00:36:08,844
(Details: The defendant defamed the plaintiff.)

498
00:36:29,634 --> 00:36:30,805
My rent.

499
00:36:31,835 --> 00:36:32,904
I said you didn't need to pay rent.

500
00:36:33,774 --> 00:36:34,974
Where did you get this?

501
00:36:34,975 --> 00:36:36,274
The box next door.

502
00:36:43,984 --> 00:36:45,085
(Chungju Apples)

503
00:36:51,625 --> 00:36:52,725
It's Sunday.

504
00:36:54,225 --> 00:36:55,954
I have to meet the client I told you about yesterday.

505
00:36:55,955 --> 00:36:57,464
(1 Box of Red Apples, Buy)

506
00:36:59,125 --> 00:37:01,035
You live your life inefficiently.

507
00:37:05,504 --> 00:37:07,875
I'm sure you can understand Ms. Seo Gye Sook.

508
00:37:08,835 --> 00:37:10,503
You filed a damage claim too.

509
00:37:10,504 --> 00:37:13,245
Wasn't it because you wanted to reveal the truth?

510
00:37:16,844 --> 00:37:19,585
A trial won't bring out the truth.

511
00:37:19,944 --> 00:37:22,214
I beg to differ. A trial can bring out the truth.

512
00:37:22,984 --> 00:37:25,225
It's what softies do.

513
00:37:25,785 --> 00:37:27,154
Those who believe that the law is justice.

514
00:37:27,294 --> 00:37:29,325
That doesn't mean revenge is justice.

515
00:37:30,864 --> 00:37:32,625
Revenge is always justice.

516
00:37:32,794 --> 00:37:36,035
Since way before the law you always talk about was created.

517
00:37:36,634 --> 00:37:39,535
Since the moment humans admitted their weakness.

518
00:37:41,875 --> 00:37:43,705
Why was the law created to begin with?

519
00:37:44,274 --> 00:37:46,745
Because personal acts of vengeance yielded miserable results.

520
00:37:47,375 --> 00:37:50,375
It was unethical and unfair.

521
00:37:51,145 --> 00:37:52,185
Are you sure about that?

522
00:37:52,814 --> 00:37:56,455
In my opinion, it is the only solution in this situation.

523
00:37:57,154 --> 00:37:59,524
Tell her to hire someone if she doesn't want to do it herself.

524
00:37:59,884 --> 00:38:01,355
Shall I give you a hitman's number?

525
00:38:03,725 --> 00:38:04,924
Do you like magic?

526
00:38:05,864 --> 00:38:07,464
Then I'll show you a magic trick...

527
00:38:07,935 --> 00:38:10,705
