542
00:39:13,826 --> 00:39:15,794
I know I'll serve jail time.

543
00:39:16,395 --> 00:39:18,404
Mr. Cho already told me everything.

544
00:39:20,535 --> 00:39:23,633
I do not understand why he sent another lawyer.

545
00:39:23,634 --> 00:39:26,205
Especially if you're here to say the exact same thing.

546
00:39:29,814 --> 00:39:30,915
Please leave.

547
00:39:31,645 --> 00:39:32,944
Don't waste your time.

548
00:39:41,924 --> 00:39:43,924
Since I'm never the one actually going through it,

549
00:39:45,594 --> 00:39:47,225
showing tears...

550
00:39:48,794 --> 00:39:50,535
and anger could be perceived...

551
00:39:52,935 --> 00:39:54,574
as disrespectful by the person who's in that situation,

552
00:39:54,575 --> 00:39:57,035
and it's nothing but shallow sympathy.

553
00:40:00,614 --> 00:40:02,674
I can't say I know what they're going through,

554
00:40:04,614 --> 00:40:06,444
nor can I say I understand their pain.

555
00:40:14,325 --> 00:40:18,864
I can't tell them that I'm hurting just as much.

556
00:40:32,875 --> 00:40:33,975
Back then,

557
00:40:36,415 --> 00:40:37,585
you were...

558
00:40:38,285 --> 00:40:39,515
the person going through it.

559
00:41:18,024 --> 00:41:19,424
Don't worry about me. Just go.

560
00:41:21,294 --> 00:41:22,625
Mom, I don't want you...

561
00:41:24,665 --> 00:41:26,964
to suffer anymore.

562
00:42:39,665 --> 00:42:40,904
Hello.

563
00:42:56,484 --> 00:42:57,524
Excuse me.

564
00:42:57,825 --> 00:43:00,055
Could you recommend a mindless book?

565
00:43:06,024 --> 00:43:07,634
("Cat Bookstore")

566
00:43:44,535 --> 00:43:46,165
When are you going to quit visiting?

567
00:43:47,265 --> 00:43:48,934
I perfectly understand...

568
00:43:48,935 --> 00:43:50,435
No, you don't!

569
00:43:51,274 --> 00:43:53,375
How would you understand?

570
00:43:54,245 --> 00:43:55,475
I frustrate you, don't I?

571
00:43:56,575 --> 00:43:58,914
You think I'm some ignorant lady...

572
00:43:58,915 --> 00:44:00,645
who doesn't even know the law.

573
00:44:02,214 --> 00:44:06,355
This may be one of many cases that you take,

574
00:44:06,884 --> 00:44:08,094
but to me,

575
00:44:09,495 --> 00:44:12,194
this is the death of my one and only child.

576
00:44:12,464 --> 00:44:14,895
This case will haunt me until the day I die.

577
00:44:15,435 --> 00:44:18,734
This case sets fire...

578
00:44:19,535 --> 00:44:23,305
to my heart thousands of times a day.

579
00:44:27,174 --> 00:44:28,614
You don't have to settle.

580
00:44:31,085 --> 00:44:33,285
I'm merely your spokesman.

581
00:44:34,785 --> 00:44:37,254
Whatever it is you want, tell me. I'll listen...

582
00:44:38,484 --> 00:44:40,825
and do what I can as your lawyer.

583
00:44:43,125 --> 00:44:44,864
(Put the books back!)

584
00:44:46,325 --> 00:44:47,524
Welcome.

585
00:44:52,335 --> 00:44:53,335
Where's your room?

586
00:44:55,634 --> 00:44:57,234
Do you mean the computer room?

587
00:45:00,274 --> 00:45:01,314
In the back.

588
00:45:03,344 --> 00:45:05,044
I need you to do something for me.

589
00:45:07,444 --> 00:45:08,455
Come inside.

590
00:45:15,424 --> 00:45:17,793
- Come on. - No!

591
00:45:17,794 --> 00:45:19,394
(Dongsan Kindergarten)

592
00:45:19,395 --> 00:45:20,724
Listen to your teacher.

593
00:45:20,725 --> 00:45:22,733
Ask me whatever you want to eat.

594
00:45:22,734 --> 00:45:24,534
I want to have steak today.

595
00:45:24,535 --> 00:45:26,935
Sure. We'll go to your favourite restaurant tonight.

596
00:45:27,205 --> 00:45:29,074
And I want a game console.

597
00:45:29,075 --> 00:45:30,634
We're rich.

598
00:45:33,404 --> 00:45:34,943
Don't ever say that.

599
00:45:34,944 --> 00:45:36,015
Say what?

600
00:45:37,944 --> 00:45:40,785
I'll buy you that game console,

601
00:45:41,355 --> 00:45:42,514
so don't mention the insurance money.

602
00:45:42,515 --> 00:45:44,185
I want game disks too.

603
00:45:44,654 --> 00:45:46,924
- I get it. - And steak!

604
00:45:47,254 --> 00:45:48,495
I will!

605
00:45:48,955 --> 00:45:50,923
And don't let Dad eat it.

606
00:45:50,924 --> 00:45:54,594
Dad finished all my food last time, and I had nothing to eat.

607
00:45:55,335 --> 00:45:57,094
If you do that again...

608
00:45:59,964 --> 00:46:01,575
I told you not to hit me.

609
00:46:01,674 --> 00:46:03,273
You can't eat it too.

610
00:46:03,274 --> 00:46:04,875
I get it!

611
00:46:05,844 --> 00:46:07,874
- Good morning. - Hello.

612
00:46:07,875 --> 00:46:11,114
Sin Woo, you must have a big appetite.

613
00:46:11,444 --> 00:46:14,484
Apparently. Still, you should share with your parents.

614
00:46:15,754 --> 00:46:18,555
We do share. He only says that.

615
00:46:19,125 --> 00:46:20,125
Let's go.

616
00:46:22,794 --> 00:46:25,293
I'm so worried that my kid will be in his class.

617
00:46:25,294 --> 00:46:26,495
So am I.

618
00:46:27,165 --> 00:46:30,734
We have a very important guest today.

619
00:46:31,364 --> 00:46:34,975
She majored in Child Psychology at Brown University.

620
00:46:35,205 --> 00:46:37,844
Affiliated with the San Francisco Government,

621
00:46:38,575 --> 00:46:42,773
Kid's Heart is a center that takes care of youth mental health,

622
00:46:42,774 --> 00:46:46,044
and she's been successfully running it.

623
00:46:46,314 --> 00:46:48,785
Please welcome Dr. Courtney Kwon.

624
00:46:55,455 --> 00:46:58,524
I'm Courtney Kwon, a child psychology specialist.

625
00:46:58,594 --> 00:47:00,765
It's a pleasure to meet you.

626
00:47:06,265 --> 00:47:07,834
I've observed...

627
00:47:07,835 --> 00:47:10,835
the parents and the children on their way to school.

628
00:47:10,975 --> 00:47:14,645
And I've noticed something quite significant.

629
00:47:18,915 --> 00:47:20,785
Will you introduce yourself?

630
00:47:21,384 --> 00:47:22,814
- Me? - Yes.

631
00:47:23,455 --> 00:47:26,024
What is your son's name?

632
00:47:27,524 --> 00:47:29,094
It's Choi Sin Woo.

633
00:47:29,455 --> 00:47:30,594
I see.

634
00:47:32,294 --> 00:47:34,794
He certainly stood out.

635
00:47:36,265 --> 00:47:39,503
An abnormal appetite, self-centered thinking,

636
00:47:39,504 --> 00:47:42,435
limited vocabulary, and violent inclination.

637
00:47:43,174 --> 00:47:44,904
He's not that bad.

638
00:47:45,205 --> 00:47:46,745
That's what is seen...

639
00:47:46,975 --> 00:47:49,214
from average people.

640
00:47:50,375 --> 00:47:52,915
But here's what I sense from him.

641
00:47:53,185 --> 00:47:56,084
Super stimulus, extrasensory manifestation,

642
00:47:56,085 --> 00:47:58,555
and triggered introversion and extroversion.

643
00:47:59,285 --> 00:48:02,994
These are qualities found in children with Einstein's cell,

644
00:48:02,995 --> 00:48:05,325
namely, the genius cell.

645
00:48:07,725 --> 00:48:10,765
All parents desire their children's specialness.

646
00:48:10,964 --> 00:48:13,434
The moment their children are acknowledged...

647
00:48:13,435 --> 00:48:16,375
as superior to other children,

648
00:48:16,634 --> 00:48:18,544
that becomes a trophy of its own.

649
00:48:19,044 --> 00:48:21,444
It may sound preposterous, but you'll see it soon.

650
00:48:22,015 --> 00:48:25,084
The more foolish the parents are, the likelier they are...

651
00:48:25,085 --> 00:48:28,355
to sell everything they've got to pursue that fantasy.

652
00:48:34,085 --> 00:48:35,325
(Child Psychology Specialist, Courtney Kwon)

653
00:48:37,555 --> 00:48:41,594
Your son has recently experienced a close person's death, hasn't he?

654
00:48:42,665 --> 00:48:44,634
If so, it's now or never.

655
00:48:46,205 --> 00:48:49,004
This will be a turning point in Sin Woo's life.

656
00:48:51,944 --> 00:48:53,174
Here.

657
00:48:58,785 --> 00:49:02,415
We honestly raise our children with love.

658
00:49:08,225 --> 00:49:10,654
Do you have two children?

659
00:49:11,794 --> 00:49:12,825
- Yes. - Yes.

660
00:49:15,134 --> 00:49:16,835
Go away. Stop taking pictures of her.

661
00:49:19,605 --> 00:49:21,605
You're hiding something from me.

662
00:49:22,634 --> 00:49:25,204
I will conduct individual interviews on all the family members...

663
00:49:25,205 --> 00:49:26,904
by the end of the week.

664
00:49:27,105 --> 00:49:30,113
I must know everything about what is currently going on,

665
00:49:30,114 --> 00:49:32,414
what has happened, and what's going to happen,

666
00:49:32,415 --> 00:49:33,645
within this family.

667
00:49:33,984 --> 00:49:35,915
As I mentioned, your son's life...

668
00:49:36,384 --> 00:49:38,524
depends on this period.

669
00:49:42,625 --> 00:49:44,055
(Update Error)

670
00:49:46,495 --> 00:49:47,564
What are you staring at?

671
00:49:48,294 --> 00:49:51,504
I just can't get it to update.

672
00:49:52,035 --> 00:49:53,105
Let me.

673
00:49:59,205 --> 00:50:00,274
Look at that.

674
00:50:00,844 --> 00:50:02,975
You already have the original app.

675
00:50:03,814 --> 00:50:06,444
Delete these two, and...

676
00:50:06,645 --> 00:50:07,685
Hang on.

677
00:50:18,633 --> 00:50:21,003
- Attorney Han, please check... - Sorry.

678
00:50:21,263 --> 00:50:23,702
Talk to me later. I'm late for a meeting.

679
00:50:26,343 --> 00:50:29,072
Please take into consideration that our client was...

680
00:50:29,073 --> 00:50:33,312
going through severe mental anguish due to her son's death.

681
00:50:33,843 --> 00:50:36,451
The protest is her way of satisfying her grudge...

682
00:50:36,452 --> 00:50:37,852
and finding mental peace.

683
00:50:44,863 --> 00:50:47,093
She never meant to harm anyone.

684
00:50:48,792 --> 00:50:51,331
Does that mean that she'll keep protesting?

685
00:50:51,332 --> 00:50:52,503
I'll talk her out of it.

686
00:50:52,903 --> 00:50:55,673
But she'll need some time until she finds peace.

687
00:50:55,972 --> 00:50:58,741
The ban on broadcasting it has been approved,

688
00:50:58,742 --> 00:51:00,073
so please understand.

689
00:51:01,772 --> 00:51:03,412
(Park and Cue Law Firm)

690
00:51:04,772 --> 00:51:07,783
Our client has also mentally suffered.

691
00:51:08,013 --> 00:51:09,752
It can be stressful to be accused...

692
00:51:09,753 --> 00:51:11,253
of murder.

693
00:51:11,582 --> 00:51:15,352
Moreover, Ms. Seo asked them to adopt Myung Hoon.

694
00:51:15,553 --> 00:51:17,693
The accident occurred while they were taking care of him.

695
00:51:17,823 --> 00:51:20,292
She doesn't have the right to defame them for it.

696
00:51:20,892 --> 00:51:22,033
I'm aware.

697
00:51:38,613 --> 00:51:40,943
(Seo Gye Sook: "Thank you for everything, Mr. Han.")

698
00:51:45,923 --> 00:51:47,883
("Thank you for everything, Mr. Han.")

699
00:52:20,952 --> 00:52:21,992
Ms. Seo.

700
00:52:25,022 --> 00:52:26,093
No.

701
00:52:27,122 --> 00:52:29,392
Think about Myung Hoon, and stop.

702
00:52:33,162 --> 00:52:34,903
Unless I do this,

703
00:52:36,102 --> 00:52:38,102
I'm just a mom...

704
00:52:39,272 --> 00:52:41,673
who sent her son to her friend to save herself.

705
00:52:42,272 --> 00:52:45,741
I didn't even care what he ate or how he dressed.

706
00:52:45,742 --> 00:52:48,383
I didn't even care how he slept.

707
00:52:59,823 --> 00:53:01,492
My poor baby...

708
00:53:02,792 --> 00:53:07,003
told me with his whole being that he didn't want to go to them.

709
00:53:08,233 --> 00:53:11,503
I ignored and turned away.

710
00:53:12,073 --> 00:53:15,472
If the likes of me don't kill myself...

711
00:53:16,613 --> 00:53:19,412
My poor Myung Hoon.

712
00:53:20,213 --> 00:53:24,452
Who will avenge his wrongful death?

713
00:53:30,053 --> 00:53:32,021
(June 14, 2022)

714
00:53:32,022 --> 00:53:33,991
(I asked how Myung Hoon was doing.)

715
00:53:33,992 --> 00:53:35,732
(Kim Bo Ra already had a plan.)

716
00:53:35,733 --> 00:53:37,392
(They didn't tell me Myung Hoon was dead.)

717
00:53:41,233 --> 00:53:43,602
We can reopen the case if we find physical evidence.

718
00:53:46,673 --> 00:53:49,972
To do that, you must stay strong.

719
00:53:54,283 --> 00:53:58,722
I miss my poor baby so much.

720
00:54:00,522 --> 00:54:04,022
If I could turn back time...

721
00:54:04,753 --> 00:54:07,693
to the day I last saw him...

722
00:54:08,863 --> 00:54:09,863
Then...

723
00:54:10,963 --> 00:54:12,003
Then...

724
00:54:12,202 --> 00:54:13,202
Eat up.

725
00:54:14,303 --> 00:54:16,403
Eat lots of veggies too.

726
00:54:16,872 --> 00:54:18,202
Chew it well.

727
00:54:21,972 --> 00:54:24,513
I sent money for a new tee.

728
00:54:25,312 --> 00:54:26,883
Did your stepmom not buy you one?

729
00:54:29,952 --> 00:54:31,153
I should call her.

730
00:54:31,753 --> 00:54:33,153
Don't call.

731
00:54:38,053 --> 00:54:39,423
Will you go somewhere on holiday?

732
00:54:39,992 --> 00:54:41,693
- Yes. - Where?

733
00:54:42,863 --> 00:54:44,463
To some valley stream.

734
00:54:44,832 --> 00:54:48,402
Even a trip like that must cost a lot...

735
00:54:48,403 --> 00:54:49,772
for a family of five.

736
00:54:51,303 --> 00:54:53,971
I'll send some extra next week...

737
00:54:53,972 --> 00:54:56,042
No, wait.

738
00:55:01,213 --> 00:55:02,952
Not next week.

739
00:55:03,153 --> 00:55:04,613
- Mom. - Yes?

740
00:55:07,182 --> 00:55:09,693
Why did you have me?

741
00:55:14,492 --> 00:55:16,193
What do you mean?

742
00:55:16,763 --> 00:55:19,162
I just want to know.

743
00:55:23,932 --> 00:55:25,803
I keep dreaming of him.

744
00:55:28,003 --> 00:55:32,042
As he sinks to the bottom of the cold stream,

745
00:55:33,812 --> 00:55:35,312
Myung Hoon...

746
00:55:37,182 --> 00:55:38,952
keeps asking...

747
00:55:41,952 --> 00:55:43,152
(My son died a year after he was adopted.)

748
00:55:43,153 --> 00:55:45,392
why I gave birth to him.

749
00:56:20,693 --> 00:56:21,792
My goodness.

750
00:56:24,292 --> 00:56:25,463
How come...

751
00:56:26,332 --> 00:56:28,033
You passed out in the street.

752
00:56:28,832 --> 00:56:30,102
Why are you here?

753
00:56:31,233 --> 00:56:35,002
I happened to call you right at that moment.

754
00:56:35,003 --> 00:56:36,113
It was a stroke of luck.

755
00:56:37,343 --> 00:56:38,372
Hang on.

756
00:56:38,783 --> 00:56:41,042
I wonder which of the nurses I talked to.

757
00:56:41,613 --> 00:56:43,483
She had a beautiful voice.

758
00:56:44,852 --> 00:56:46,952
Is that her over there?

759
00:56:47,622 --> 00:56:49,022
Why did you call me?

760
00:56:50,452 --> 00:56:52,562
Oh, the studio apartment flooded,

761
00:56:53,062 --> 00:56:55,932
and I can't seem to locate Lee Ro Um.

762
00:57:01,003 --> 00:57:03,173
You must be under a lot of stress.

763
00:57:03,673 --> 00:57:05,443
Do you see a shrink?

764
00:57:06,772 --> 00:57:07,772
(12th, Calendar)

765
00:57:13,883 --> 00:57:15,451
Considering the state you're in,

766
00:57:15,452 --> 00:57:17,452
I think you should find a new shrink.

767
00:57:17,812 --> 00:57:19,721
Consultations cost a fortune and look at you.

768
00:57:19,722 --> 00:57:21,952
My doctor is just fine.

769
00:57:22,193 --> 00:57:23,193
My gosh.

770
00:57:23,452 --> 00:57:25,053
What patient's this loyal?

771
00:57:25,792 --> 00:57:29,292
Take the opportunity to switch to someone good.

772
00:57:31,662 --> 00:57:32,803
Stay out of it.

773
00:57:35,332 --> 00:57:38,272
I came all the way here for you.

774
00:57:41,272 --> 00:57:42,343
Thank you.

775
00:57:43,343 --> 00:57:44,412
You're welcome.

776
00:57:45,613 --> 00:57:47,343
(Moran Hospital)

777
00:57:49,383 --> 00:57:50,682
You can go now.

778
00:57:57,952 --> 00:57:59,323
Okay, fine.

779
00:58:05,332 --> 00:58:06,403
I mean it.

780
00:58:07,162 --> 00:58:09,202
I called a cab. You can go.

781
00:58:09,702 --> 00:58:12,903
Our ancestors said no meant yes.

782
00:58:14,573 --> 00:58:16,943
You look so weak and frail.

783
00:58:17,272 --> 00:58:19,113
You'd flop with one nudge.

784
00:58:19,582 --> 00:58:22,612
How do you think I'd feel to leave you...

785
00:58:22,613 --> 00:58:24,053
struggle to get home?

786
00:58:25,983 --> 00:58:27,522
What are you on about?

787
00:58:28,082 --> 00:58:30,322
I'm fine, and a cab's on the way.

788
00:58:30,323 --> 00:58:32,022
Our ancestors said...

789
00:58:32,463 --> 00:58:35,193
a vehement denial was a strong affirmation.

790
00:58:36,162 --> 00:58:38,192
What ancestor said...

791
00:58:38,193 --> 00:58:41,332
I can't believe I must watch over a lawyer too.

792
00:58:41,932 --> 00:58:42,932
Goodness.

793
00:58:43,772 --> 00:58:47,173
I'm such a great probation officer.

794
00:58:50,513 --> 00:58:51,573
Leave me alone now.

795
00:58:54,443 --> 00:58:56,253
Yes means no.

796
00:59:02,253 --> 00:59:03,423
Take me home, then.

797
00:59:03,992 --> 00:59:05,022
Yes.

798
00:59:13,503 --> 00:59:14,562
Go.

799
00:59:19,242 --> 00:59:21,142
Isn't it time you go home?

800
00:59:23,912 --> 00:59:25,142
You're the frigid type.

801
00:59:25,983 --> 00:59:27,513
I'll make sure you go inside.

802
00:59:46,463 --> 00:59:47,463
Let's agree on...

803
00:59:47,832 --> 00:59:49,272
a few things.

804
00:59:50,803 --> 00:59:53,502
Things you must do to protect yourself...

805
00:59:53,503 --> 00:59:55,772
when you deal with Lee Ro Um.

806
00:59:59,742 --> 01:00:00,783
First,

807
01:00:01,343 --> 01:00:04,312
don't go against your principles as a lawyer.

808
01:00:09,923 --> 01:00:10,952
Ms. Lee.

809
01:00:11,222 --> 01:00:12,263
Second,

810
01:00:13,363 --> 01:00:15,463
keep her out of your personal domain.

811
01:00:15,963 --> 01:00:17,162
What's all this?

812
01:00:17,963 --> 01:00:19,003
Third,

813
01:00:20,332 --> 01:00:22,872
do not overlook anything illegal.

814
01:00:23,602 --> 01:00:25,332
Yoo Myung Hoon's insurance payout.

815
01:00:27,272 --> 01:00:28,343
Lastly,

816
01:00:30,173 --> 01:00:31,213
never...

817
01:00:32,483 --> 01:00:34,042
let your guard down.

